<br>
Learn to quad, its easy <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/napalm2/gumbum/balicos.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quikpick>Quikpick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 660<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 10:05 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: cant quad -&gt; nothing worth now ?</span><hr size=1> Well....some wizards never learn to quad. Exp may be great but it can get boring.<br>
<br>
If you can handle agro and mana management within groups/raids, then I'd say you are not a worthless wizard.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p><P><p align="center"><strong><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55973"><font color="#00CC00">Sage Quikpick Emberlore</a></font><BR><font color="#999999">Sorceress of Chronology</font></strong><BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jago668>jago668</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 10:17 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: cant quad -&gt; nothing worth now ?</span><hr size=1> If you can do your job correctly in a raid or group you aren't worthless.  However I do agree that it is a useful skill to have, and you should really try to learn.  If you don't have jboots or a staff of temperate flux, get them.  Then go to some lowbie area and learn to quad or greens.  Eastern Wastes comes to mind of a really easy place to quad in.  Go there and keep a root up along with snare. <p>Aahzmandius
"The best feign death always seems to be the one when corpse appears after your name."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delfontes>Delfontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 10:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Quadding, I believe, is an Essential skill.<br>
<br>
It defines the abilities of a Wizard.<br>
<br>
12 levels ago or so I thought the same as you, I'd never quad, because I'd die...<br>
<br>
Then I got my flux staff, a soloable quest in a day at lvl 50... and should have gotten it at level 30 with a group.<br>
<br>
Now I am sooo thankful for the experience, and the knowledge.<br>
<br>
Basically you're learning a very difficult kite, and it can be of use in groups, if a mob is unmezzable and/or unrootable... You can CC it, and if you're an experienced quadder, you can likely CC it better than anyone else in the group.<br>
<br>
It is difficult, yes, but like wax on/wax off, skills can have more uses than we even pay attention to.<br>
<br>
P.S. J-boots, don't even think about T-boots, seriously.  The ability to refresh J-boots when they start flashing mid kite without slowing down is what kept me alive at least a dozen times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=armagedsnr>Armaged SnR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 12:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Quadding, I believe, is an Essential skill.<br>
<br>
It defines the abilities of a Wizard.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
By no means is it required nor does it define a wizard.<br>
I know level 65 wizards that cannot single kite let alone kite 4 at once.  Yet they're still 65 with good guilds, gear, and AA's.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>P.S. J-boots, don't even think about T-boots, seriously. The ability to refresh J-boots when they start flashing mid kite without slowing down is what kept me alive at least a dozen times.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again, another misnomer.  Some of us never wanted to do a BS camp for something that is slower than SOW potions and doesn't work indoors.  The same folks that learned by accident that quadding Wyverns in CS is in fact doable with just run2 because the SOW potions ran out.<br>
<br>
That's almost as bad as saying Ice Comet or Concussion are class defining spells.  Some folks never wasted their mana casting IC with it's poor recast/mana/damage ration opting for fast casting more effecient draughts.  And some of us have never had, wanted, or needed concussion......<br>
<br>
That being said <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Quadding isn't hard to learn depending on where and how you try.  It's also a great way to actually get something down while /lfg. <p>Aazumar Dracostarr<br>
Sage Arcanist of Solusek<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Valiant Crusaders</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=346949" target="top">My Stuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 3:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Learn in EW after you get your Tstaff, if you have Run 3 then that works, use sow to learn. <br>
<br>
Keep in mind that unless your fairly good a few deaths (exodus keep them lower) are to be expected if you try quadding in a compleatly new area to you. <br>
<br>
Do you need to learn, no. But when your LFG and there is quad material you make exp faster then singlekiting and much faster then sitting doing nothing. <br>
<br>
Up to you but its a neat trick to have in your bag, and one that can help in some circumstances.<br>
<br>
F3 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gyorg@graffeswizardcompilation>Gyorg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 4:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> quadding</span><hr size=1> Quadding skill is of no value to anyone but ones self. Unless you plan to power level someone by duoing and letting them leech xp. I can't think of any way that someone could 'help you quad', other than buff you beforehand. If they nuked too, even with an AE, you risk them getting aggro and screwing things up. <br>
So it is of no value in a group or raid, totally different sets of skills are required there. The main one being doing juggling as-much-damage-as-you-can-do with aggro-control and mana-usage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delfontes>Delfontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 11:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> I wont get into an argument here over how you'd consider someone who can't single kite at level 65 a good player....<br>
<br>
but I will talk a bit about j-boots<br>
<br>
Who said camp?  You can camp it, like most wizards do, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>or</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you can buy an MQ.<br>
<br>
On most servers an MQ for J-boots wont run you more than the cost of T-boots.   <br>
<br>
J-boots were why I was able to go from 50-60 without stopping for run3 til I hit 60. (had run 1 somewhere in there to outrun zone trash in dungeons).<br>
<br>
Anyone who thinks T-boots are as good as J-boots for quadding must never have had J-boots.  Even Druids I've known talk about sow or soe fading at the wrong time, and dying.  I can only laugh at that, because j-boots <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>can not fade</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> at the wrong time.  Not to mention the free instaclick buff for outdoor dispellers. <br>
<br>
Thats all I have to say about that, hehe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bayler>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 12:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> It's a trivial matter to refresh your boots before each quad.  I do this - with JBoots - just because I don't want to take the time to open my inventory screen and click while grouping the quad.  (I could put JBoots in a hotkey slot, but I've got more important things I'd rather put there.)<br>
 <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
Tessally - 54 Nun of Solusek Ro - Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=styphon>styphon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 12:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Quadding is simply a method for you to get xp for yourself; nothing more. I'm a pretty good quadder and as such, leveled fairly quickly. However, I missed out on a lot of fun times with my guildies because I rarely grouped. Groups have a hard time matching the xp you can get quadding. <br>
<br>
If you know how to handle yourself in groups and raids, controlling aggro, managing mana, rooting/stunning mobs if they go after healers, and evacing when needed, you are not a worthless wizard- you're just more social than most of us. =)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lizzari>lizzari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 12:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soloing and Quad-Kiting</span><hr size=1> sorry for late reply. but i can only post one time per day *CRY*. i allready asked the admin 3 times now, to upgrade my status, but he cant/wont do it.<br>
