=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/03 8:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> If you have problems with it, it could be a computer or connection issue too. I had a terribly slow computer for a long time. When I tried to quad kite, it often took longer to cast snare (from the time I was within distance to cast) than it did for the mobs to catch up and hit me. I got a new computer and tried it again and it was cake <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=veli9>Veli9</A> at: 6/8/03 5:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1517<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/03 2:55 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lll</span><hr size=1> Liz, quadding isn't all that.  Don't sweat it if its not your thing, really.  Join a fun guild and/or find good grouping partners. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=northyr>NOR Thyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/9/03 12:28 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lll</span><hr size=1> LOL, I asked this very same question not too long ago, and got much the same reply that you're getting here. Let me throw my 2cp in and give you the benefit of what I've learned since then.<br>
<br>
I *hated* the idea of quadding because of a number of encounters with quadding druids who dumped bad pulls on my shaman more than once.  I was 100% against learning to quad and planned to never do it, even though a guildmate of mine who's main wizzie was approximately the same level as me kept pushing me to try it.  Among other things, I figured that my poor connection quality and general bad luck would get me killed alot.<br>
<br>
Finally I asked here, and listened to the reasoning of the pro-quadders.  I decided that if the wizzie community at large was so solidly behind quadding, then it would be valuable to me to at least make a good, honest attempt at learning to do it.<br>
<br>
I started out slowly, building up to a quad, on zelniaks by kiting 2-3 of them at a time.  It was hard, it was ugly and I died a few times, but I learned a bit.  Then I moved to the outside of ToFS and tried snow guardians (which were still dblue to me at the time).  I jumped straight into quadding without trying to build up to it slowly and suddenly it all came together for me and I easily finished 2 quads on one bar of mana for about 12% xp.  Prior to that I'd been getting all of 6% for a full bar of mana single kiting.  Flushed with success I went to EW and tried it on the ulthorks..my xp to mana ratio jumped up even higher, I was getting almost a full yellow of xp for one bar of mana now.<br>
<br>
Needless to say, I'm quite hooked on quadding now..and would highly recommend any wizard try it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=614716">Thyrbit Firefrog</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zertez>zertez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 1:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>  Re: lll</span><hr size=1>  By no means are you worthless for not knowing how to quad, it is far from essential, can it be useful yes but it is not a must learn skill.<br>
<br>
 Wizard bring a lot to groups and plenty of my friends have never quadded more than once or twice they just do not like it. They are lvl 62 plus with 150 something aa, so I think they are doing just fine. Get out and meet people and make friends, when you have a good network of friends finding groups is easy and doing this instead of quadding will put you in better shape when the time comes you want to group more.<br>
<br>
 In some cases I think wizards who quad exclusively hurts them more than it helps, when you reach 58 or so and want groups not having the networks of friends or grouping skills that you need as a wizard, you have to settle for a lot of random pickup groups. Think we all know how horrible some of these groups can be <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
 When you log on having mainly grouping experience you will have more options of groups to choose <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . The main thing is have fun, if you dont like to quad dont. Some here like to complain about finding groups but if you spend a lot of time grouping, groups come easy especially after 60 when a wizard is a beast <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zertez>zertez</A> at: 6/10/03 1:29 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balicosdalinar>Balicos Dalinar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 3:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Re: lll</span><hr size=1> &quot;Hi, Im Balicos and Im a quadder.&quot;<br>
