I quadded since I had BoF. Now I know only my guildies and very few others. Had a great time quadding and really honed the skill to an art in my opinion, BUT... It seems tomorrow that will all change and Ill have to meet new and interesting people..... Scary... <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/napalm2/gumbum/balicos.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calandria0>Calandria0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 6:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Re: lll</span><hr size=1> I *hate* soloing. But, around 53 I took the time to learn to quad beause I just wasn't finding groups. It works, I still hate doing it, but it is certainly a useful skill to have. <br>
<br>
However, I do it a bit different than others. I've never owned a tstaff. Never realy thought it was worthwhile. I pull with snare. That way, should my puter lag after I pull, I don't die before I get a chance to snare the critters. <br>
